<br>
“What?” he asked. <br>
<br>
Tyl fumed, her anger rising even faster as she noticed his blank stare replaced with a smirk, much like the one he flashed at her in the depths of Muire tomb. That look also reminded her of the importance of the information this man claimed to have. <br>
<br>
“Do not worry about your friend,” the rogue suddenly began, “she is merely asleep. We could not have her following us, much less hearing about our plan.” <br>
<br>
“OUR plan?” Tyl reiterated, skepticism clear on her face. <br>
<br>
“Well, maybe not OUR plan. But one you will come to accept, if you ever want to recover your precious book.” <br>
<br>
Tyl looked to her friend, Evelynne; now sound asleep on the floor. She hoped Eve would not hold this against her when she awoke. <br>
<br>
“So what is OUR plan?” Tyl said, defeated. <br>
<br>
